snippet.textDisplay:
Sonos having their own voice control would be actually a great thing, if they restrict it to playback control features of music and podcasts alone and allow for Alexa and the Google Assistant to answer dumb questions and set timers for pizza cookery. The playback control features that Sonos has access to through Amazon and Google are hamstrung by the two companies in order to make those experiences better on their Echo and Google Home devices respectively. I have used both on my Sonos One from day 1 that each were available and they are a headache. 

Equivalently to how using the Sonos app is better at doing music control from various services (Spotify, Amazon Music Unlimited, YT music) vs using the music services base apps to control music is a better, higher functioning experience, I think that having Sonos voice control could be a better experience than Alexa and OK Google. Ps I hate the Sonos app interface but it never fails to work.
